  "prompt": "What are some things to try when your car key won't turn in the ignition?",
  "response": "Here are some things to try when your car key won't turn in the ignition:\n\n1. Wiggle the steering wheel\n- Sometimes the steering wheel locks and prevents key rotation\n- Gently turn the wheel left and right while trying to turn the key\n\n2. Check the gear position\n- Ensure the car is in \"Park\" or \"Neutral\"\n- Shifter might need to be precisely positioned\n\n3. Jiggle the key gently\n- Slightly move the key up and down while turning\n- Could help align tumblers inside the ignition\n\n4. Check the key\n- Examine key for damage or wear\n- Try a spare key if available\n\n5. Lubricate the lock\n- Use graphite powder or silicon-based lubricant\n- Avoid oil-based lubricants which can attract dirt\n\n6. Check battery\n- Low battery might prevent electrical systems from functioning correctly\n- Try jump-starting the car\n\n7. Inspect battery terminals\n- Ensure they're clean and connected properly\n\n8. Check for debris in the keyhole\n- Carefully clean out any visible dirt or obstructions\n\n9. Tap the key cylinder\n- Gently tap the ignition with the key inserted\n\nIf these methods don't work, consult a professional mechanic or locksmith.",
